The nature and importance of the active learning. The different possibilities for the active learning process. The problem solving, open-ended problems. The activity-based geometry learning. Reading strategies and silent videos. Games in the mathematics lesson. The computer as a tool for the activities.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The students gain the skills of the mathematics learning and teaching with active methods through personal experience.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing this course the student
1.	knows the features of active learning; 
2.	knows different methods for active learning;
3.	can use different strategies of critical thinking by solving tasks;
4.	can complete and solve open-ended problems connected with independent erecting of mathematical hypothesis;
5.	can use games in mathematics;
6.	can organize learning mathematics through action;
7.	has acquired different group working experiences for learning mathematics;
8.     can analyze and reflect on his/her actions.
